values:
Hello!

So it's official, I'm moving back to Austin! I got a job working at the ACC South Campus, as an Assistant in Admissions. I haven't met my boss yet but she sent me a very nice e-mail inviting me to lunch on my orientation day. 
I'll be back May 9th (Mother's Day) to live with my parents till the beginning of June then it's a flight back up to Lubbock to move John and Brady down to our new apartment. I'm super excited!

So if you live in the Austin area and want to see me, drop me a line!

I am so excited about moving back! It looks like it'll happen in late May/June depending on a few things. 

I found out from the family CPA today that I owe the IRS $619 for taxes, YUCK! It's because I'm a government employee so they don't with-hold very much from my paychecks. So, I need to start saving that money up so that I can pay it by April 14th. 

The plan is to move down with John and Brady. I'm super excited about living with both of them! Because of my past I've recently been super aware of not just assuming things because the relationship is going well, so I'm sure John is getting a little tired me asking every few weeks; "Are you SURE you want to keep living with me in Austin?". He always smiles, tells me not to worry so much, and that yes he does. 
Brady is moving down to Austin as well since he's fallen in love with the city every time we go for a visit and he's looking at trying to get some sort of job with his Electronic Comm degree. Brady and I have similar outlooks when it comes to how a house should be. None of us want things to be perfectly clean all the time but if the sink is full, go ahead and take the five minutes to empty it into the dishwasher...
Plus, Brady will help make sure John and I don't become shut in's, because we tend to stay at home even now, and keep us young at heart even if we have work at 8 am.

Here are the two possibilities of moving to Austin:

1) Being accepted to the UT Art History program. It would be cool to actually have the chance to get a job one day with my degree, and an MA would greatly help that. I'd have to get a bunch of student loans and cross my fingers at finding some sort of part time job on campus.

2) Not accepted and have to find another normal job in Austin. This is much more likely to happen. Right now I'd really take any job that was $11/hr with benefits, but the job market in Austin is really hard right now so I'd be lucky to find SOMETHING.


And one last speed bump that really has me worried is JP. 

I know in the past I've complained about JP a lot and me and him have even talked about the fact that we couldn't live together again. But, he's recently asked about John and I moving down to Austin. I up front told him no, I don't want you to move in with us. But, I did tell him that if he really wanted to come to Austin he could crash on our couch till he found a job. The Brady being a roommate was a new development since then. 

I don't want JP to hate me or John. John would be so disappointed if he and JP weren't friends anymore, he thinks of JP as his best friend. I want to be able to hang out with JP in Austin, to see him do well on his own.

I know I made a lot of goals here. A lot of promises to lose weight, handle my money better ect. 

But this time, it's gonna be different.

I have a very specific goal in mind. Well, it's sorta a few goals in one. 

Here's the list:

Get rid of advances from my bank and get back on track with my money.

Put $500 in savings by March 25th.

Get down to 200 lbs by April 1st

Have $1000 in savings by May 25th.

Get down to 175 lbs by July 4th weekend.

Go to Gruene, TX with John for a few days in August/September (after the move to Austin)




The last thing is kinda planning really far ahead. We haven't made any huge plans to move to ATX together, just kind of talked about it without really talking about it. The main thing is losing the weight and saving the money. Which can in fact go hand in hand. If I spend less money on eating out then I'll be forced to just eat simple things at home. And I won't necessarily be disappointed if we don't go to Gruene, the point is currently I wouldn't want to go. I'd be too self aware to have fun.

Hello!

So everything has blown over from the other night. Me and John talked about it, he felt like a shit head, apologized a bunch and we've moved on. JP still acts like the jackass that he is, but that's just JP. He enjoys being a jackass. Which is part of why we're friends with him, don't try to even understand this logic. 

On to Christmas presents!

Yes, I know it's a few days past Christmas but John and I decided to wait till the next paycheck came in so we could get each other awesome presents. And let me tell you....I got some awesome presents.

I bought John a new stereo receiver for his system since his old one is broken, a documentary about his favorite indie cartoonist and a little hand-made book for him to write in.

I got....

an antique necklace that has three rubies on a tree branch-like-thing

an antique make up compact from 1920

three different size ceramic canisters for things like flour or sugar in the kitchen (which I really needed!)

a notepad

a nib holder

india ink

a new wallet

and a shoulder bag!

Who's boyfriend is made of awesome? My boyfriend, that's who!
